{Black has refrained from both exchanging bishops with ...Ba6 and starting the
central counterattack with ...c7-c5. preferring to put his king into safety as
soon as possible. How could he now make use of his better coordination?} 15...
g5 $1 $17 ({Immediately shaking White's stability in the centre.} 15... b5 16.
Bb3 g5 {would have been equally strong.}) 16. g4 ({White relied on this
counter blow in vain. If} 16. Qg2 g4 17. Nd2 b5 18. Bb3 {, Black can choose
whether to win a pawn on d4 or e5.}) 16... hxg4 $1 {A typical Petrosian
exchange sacrifice.} 17. Qxh8 gxf3 $1 18. Qh5 (18. Bxc6 Qxc6 19. Qxf6 Be7 20.
Qg6 Kb8 $1 {attacks the c3-knight and prepares to meet Qxe6 with ...Bc8.} 21.
Nd1 Qxc2 22. Bxg5 Nxd4 $1 $19) 18... b5 19. Nxb5 ({Desperation, as after} 19.
Bb3 fxe5 {the centre collapses.}) 19... axb5 20. Bxb5 fxe5 {and Black won.} 0-1

