{White did not play h2-h4. Can Black use this to his advantage?} 13... g5 $1 {
Of course! Due to White's poor coordination, Black can start his attack with
incomplete development.} 14. Bf1 (14. g4 $2 Nh6) 14... g4 15. Nh4 Bxh4 16. gxh4
Ne7 {Planning ...Nf5.} 17. b4 {Desperately trying to change the unfavourable
course of the game.} cxb3 18. Bd3 (18. Nxb3 $2 Bxa4 19. Nxa5 Bxd1 20. Rxb6 axb6
21. Nxb7 Bf3 $19) 18... Ng6 (18... Bxa4 19. Ba3 Nec6 $5 {[%cal Gb6d8] ,
followed by Qd8 (Kortschnoj)}) 19. Bxg6 fxg6 20. Nxb3 Bxa4 21. Qd3 Bxb3 22.
Qxg6+ Kd7 23. Qf7+ Kc8 24. Ba3 Qc6 25. Bb4 Bc2 26. Rb2 Bf5 27. Bxa5 b6 28. Bb4
Rh7 29. Qg8+ Kb7 30. Qg5 Rc8 $17 {With great play on the light squares for
Black, even though in the end White managed to hold a draw.} 1/2-1/2

