1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Bd3 {Just like in the 4.Qd3 line White tries
to keep the tension in the centre, but once again this implies waste of time.}
dxe4 {The simplest way to speed up development.} 5. Bxe4 Nf6 6. Bf3 {Hoping to
delay Black's queenside development.} (6. Bd3 {is just a loss of time and
allows Black to open the centre at his own leisure:} c5 7. dxc5 (7. Nf3 cxd4 8.
Nxd4 e5 9. Nde2 Bg4 10. f3 Be6 11. a3 Be7 12. Be3 O-O 13. O-O Nbd7 14. Ng3 Bc5
$11 {Renet,O (2507)-Ivanchuk,V (2705) Izmir 2004 (1/2, 51)}) (7. a3 Bxc3+ 8.
bxc3 Qc7 9. Nf3 O-O 10. O-O c4 11. Be2 Nbd7 12. a4 Nd5 13. Ra3 b6 $15 {Zecevic,
D-Rasidovic,S (2380) Pula 1984 (1/2, 44)}) 7... Nbd7 8. Bd2 Nxc5 9. Bb5+ (9.
Bc4 O-O 10. a3 Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Na4 $11 {Mallahi,A (2406)-Bellini,F (2486) Bled
2002 (1/2, 59)}) 9... Ncd7 10. Nf3 a6 11. Bd3 O-O 12. O-O {Averbakh,
Y-Botvinnik,M Moscow 1955 (0-1, 65)} Be7 13. Qe2 Nc5 $11) (6. Bg5 {is only a
temporary solution to the hanging e4-bishop.} c5 7. dxc5 (7. Nge2 cxd4 8. Nxd4
Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Qa5 10. Bxf6 Qxc3+ 11. Ke2 gxf6 {, and White still needs to
prove his compensation for the pawn, as his structure is imperfect and his
king exposed, too.}) 7... Qxd1+ 8. Rxd1 Nbd7 (8... Nxe4 $4 9. Rd8#) 9. Bf3
Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Nxc5 11. Ne2 Bd7 $15 {Kuzmin,G (2535)-Matlak,M (2455)
Cappelle-la-Grande 1997 (1-0, 58)}) 6... O-O 7. Nge2 ({Once again} 7. Bg5 {
is ineffective:} h6 8. Bxf6 (8. Bh4 c5 9. a3 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Nbd7 11. dxc5 Qa5
12. Qd4 e5 13. Qb4 Qxc5 14. Bxf6 Qxb4 15. axb4 Nxf6 $15 {Gunnarsson,J (2458)
-Van Kampen,R (2615) Reykjavik 2016 (0-1, 33)}) 8... Qxf6 9. Nge2 {Fiebig,T 
(2401) -Medvegy,Z (2510) Germany 2015 (1-0, 37)} c5 $11) (7. a3 {wastes
another important tempo.} Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 Re8 $5 {Preparing the central break.}
9. Bf4 (9. Ne2 e5 10. dxe5 Qxd1+ 11. Kxd1 Ng4 12. Bxg4 Bxg4 13. f3 Bd7 14. Bf4
Nc6 15. Rb1 b6 $15) 9... Nc6 10. Ne2 e5 11. Bxc6 bxc6 12. dxe5 (12. Bxe5 $2 {
Narusevicius,L (1690)-Kutkaitis,R (1665) Panevezys 2010 (1-0, 25)} Ba6 $19)
