19. Rb1 Nd5 $15) (10. a4 {With the pawn on b7 this fails to bother Black and
mainly wastes time.} Bc6 11. a5 Nbd7 12. h3 Bb5 13. dxc5 Qc7 $15 {Wang,J (2394)
-Kacheishvili,G (2578) Las Vegas 2013 (0-1, 24)}) (10. Bb2 {looks awfully
passive.} Ba4 11. O-O-O {Kosteniuk,A (2527)-Krush,I (2491) Khanty-Mansiysk
2014 (1-0, 37)} Ng4 12. Qf4 Qg5 $15) (10. Ng3 Bc6 11. dxc5 Nbd7 {Once again
Black can use the numerous weaknesses in White's camp to activate his pieces,
