looks viable, too.} 11. h3 f6 12. O-O Na5 13. Nh5 Ng6) 11. h3 {Preventing not
only ...Bg4 but also ... h7-h5.} (11. O-O h5 $1 12. h4 (12. h3 h4 13. Nh5 Bf5
14. Nxg7 Bxd3 15. cxd3 Rdg8 16. Nh5 Rxh5 17. Qxh5 Qxh3 18. g3 Rxg3+ {with a
draw by perpetual.}) 12... f6 13. a4 Rhg8 $5 $146 14. Qxh5 (14. Re1 Bg4 15. Qf4
g5 $15 16. Qxf6 $2 Rdf8 17. Qh6 gxh4 18. Nf1 h3 $19) (14. Ba3 Bg4) 14... Rh8
15. Qe2 Rxh4 16. Re1 Bf5 17. Nxf5 Nxf5 18. Qe6 Qxe6 19. Rxe6 Rdh8 20. f3 Rh1+
21. Kf2 Nd6 22. Bf1 Kd7 23. Re1 Na5 $11 {The bishops' pair is completely
neutralized since Black has two active rooks and the knights control all the
important weaknesses.}) (11. Bb5 h5 12. h4 Rde8 13. O-O Ng6 $15) (11. a4 h5 12.
h4 Bg4 13. Qf4 Ng6 14. Bxg6 fxg6 $15) 11... f6 12. O-O h5 $1 {A perfectly
justified pawn sacrifice, leading to the chronical weakening of the c4-square.}
13. Nxh5 Nf5 14. Nf4 Nh4 15. Qg3 Bf5 16. Bxf5 (16. a4 g5 17. Ne2 Rde8 18. Re1
g4 19. Bxf5 Nxf5 20. Qxg4 Reg8 21. Qf4 Rxh3 $19) 16... Nxf5 17. Qd3 $2 (17. Qg4
{is better, although after} Na5 {Black's compensation is beyond doubt.}) 17...
g5 18. Ne2 Rdg8 19. f3 Na5 $19 {With overwhelming activity in Thavandiran,S 
