1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 b6 5. Qg4 Bf8 6. h4 {Since the bishop's
incursion to g5 is likely to cause loss of time, White tries to change the
move order.} h5 $5 {This is justified by the fact that White cannot reach the
regrouping with Bg5 and Qf4 so easily with the given move order.} ({If} 6...
Ne7 7. Bg5 Ba6 (7... h5 8. Qf4) 8. Bxa6 Nxa6 9. h5 h6 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. f4 Nb4
12. O-O-O O-O-O 13. Nge2 Qd7 14. Rhf1 {, White's attacking chances look more
realistic.}) 7. Qd1 {A familiar flexible move, implying the also familiar loss
of time.} (7. Qf3 Ne7 8. Bg5 Qd7 9. Qf4 {Reaching the optimal regrouping with
the loss of a tempo, which allows Black to start his counterplay.} c5 10. Bb5
Nbc6 11. Nf3 a6 12. Bxc6 Nxc6 $11) (7. Qg3 Ne7 8. Bd3 Ba6 9. Bg5 Qd7 10. Nge2
Bxd3 11. Qxd3 Nbc6 (11... c5 $15) 12. Ng3 Ng8 13. Nce2 Be7 14. c3 Na5 15. Bxe7
{1/2-1/2 Zuriel,M (2205)-Amed,S (2208) Buenos Aires 2010}) 7... Ba6 {Since ...
h5 has placed another pawn on a light square, exchanging bishops is the most
desirable plan.} (7... c5 8. Bg5 Qd7 9. Bb5 Nc6 10. Nge2 a6 11. Bxc6 Qxc6 12.
Nf4 cxd4 13. Nce2 Qc7 (13... Bb4+ 14. Kf1 f6 $13) 14. O-O $14 (14. Nd3 Bc5 15.
Nef4 f6 16. Ng6 Rh7 $13 {Blatny,P (2470)-Psakhis,L (2565) Amsterdam 1989 (1-0,
40)}) 14... Qxe5 15. Nxd4 $36) 8. Bxa6 Nxa6 9. Bg5 Qd7 10. Nge2 (10. Qe2 Nb4
11. Nh3 Nc6 12. O-O-O {Stukopin,A (2586)-Young,A (2281) Chicago 2017 (1-0, 29)}
Nge7 13. Kb1 Nf5 14. Be3 O-O-O 15. Nf4 g6 $11) (10. Nf3 Ne7 11. Ne2 (11. Qe2
Nb4 12. a3 Nbc6 13. Nd1 Nf5 14. Qd3 Be7 15. Ne3 Nxe3 16. Bxe3 Na5 17. O-O c5 {
Husari,S (2334)-Jamrich,G (2271) Balatonlelle 2003 (1-0, 41)}) 11... Ng6 12. c3
c5 13. O-O Nb8 14. Re1 Nc6 15. Qd3 Be7 16. g3 Rc8 17. Rac1 Bxg5 18. Nxg5 Nce7
$11) 10... c5 11. Ng3 g6 12. dxc5 Nxc5 13. Qe2 Na4 14. Nxa4 Qxa4 15. c4 Qxc4
16. Qxc4 dxc4 17. Ne4 Be7 18. O-O-O {Sutovsky,E (2560)-Psakhis,L (2610) Israel
1997 (1/2-1/2, 49)} b5 19. Rd4 a6 20. Rhd1 Bxg5+ 21. hxg5 Ne7 {White does not
have anything better than forcing a draw with} 22. Rd8+ Rxd8 23. Nf6+ Kf8 24.
Rxd8+ Kg7 25. Ne8+ Kh7 $11 *

