1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 b6 5. Qg4 Bf8 6. Nh3 $5 {I remember that
many years before I started playing the French and already years after
stopping playing 1.e4, this was considered a critical test to the 4...b6
system. As we know, the knight is mainly heading for h5.} Ne7 7. Bg5 ({It is
useful to activate the bishop before advancing with the knight, as after} 7.
Nf4 {Black has} g6 $1 8. Be3 (8. Bd3 c5 9. Bb5+ Nbc6 10. O-O cxd4 11. Nce2 Bd7
12. Nd3 {Karius,T (2235)-Spiess,G (2391) Germany 2004 (0-1, 22)} h5 13. Qf4 Nf5
14. Bxc6 Bxc6 15. Nxd4 Nxd4 16. Qxd4 Rc8 17. b3 Bb5 $132) (8. Nd3 Nf5 9. Bg5
Be7 10. h4 h5 11. Qf4 Nc6 12. Ne2 Ba6 13. O-O-O Qd7 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. Kb1 O-O-O
$11 {[%cal Gf7f6] Zuse,K (2295)-Martin,T (2310) Germany 1988 (0-1, 91)}) {
Illingworth,M (2352)-Johansen,D (2444) Canberra 2012 (1/2-1/2, 35)} 8... c5 9.
Bb5+ Nbc6 10. dxc5 Bg7 11. Nd3 O-O $15 {Due to the threat ...d5-d4 Black will
retrieve the pawn soon with excellent play.}) 7... h6 $5 ({The main model game
of those times went} 7... Nbc6 8. Bb5 Bd7 9. O-O-O h6 10. Be3 a6 11. Be2 $14 {
, with a certain lack of harmony in Black's camp. Perenyi,B (2360)-Portisch,L 
(2615) Hungary 1987 (1-0, 38)}) 8. Bxe7 (8. Bh4 g5 $1 9. Bg3 Nf5 10. Bb5+ c6
11. Bd3 c5 12. dxc5 Nxg3 13. hxg3 bxc5 14. f4 Nc6 15. Bb5 Bd7 $11) (8. Be3 c5
9. dxc5 Nbc6 10. cxb6 axb6 11. Bb5 Bd7 {once again leaves White with problems
to keep his extra pawn after having given up the centre.}) 8... Qxe7 9. Nf4 $1
(9. Nxd5 $4 h5 $1 $19 10. Nxe7 hxg4 11. Nxc8 gxh3) {Vesselovsky,S (2455)
-Odesskij,I Moscow 1994 (1/2-1/2, 41)} 9... Bb7 $1 {Black continues his
development ignoring the kingside threats, which will cost White a lot of time.
} 10. Nh5 Nc6 11. Nxg7+ (11. O-O-O O-O-O $11 12. Nxg7 $2 Rg8 $19) 11... Bxg7
12. Qxg7 O-O-O 13. Qg4 (13. O-O-O Rdg8 14. Qf6 Qxf6 15. exf6 Rg6 $11 16. g3
Rxf6 17. Rd2 Ne7 18. Bg2 Nf5 19. Re1 Nd6 $11) 13... f6 $1 {Being by far better
developed, Black has to open the centre.} 14. exf6 Qxf6 15. O-O-O Rhg8 16. Nxd5
(16. Qf3 Qxf3 17. gxf3 e5 $11) 16... Rxg4 17. Nxf6 Rf4 18. d5 Nb4 19. a3 Nxc2
20. dxe6 Rxd1+ 21. Kxd1 Rxf6 22. Kxc2 Rxf2+ 23. Kc3 Kd8 $11 *

