effective solution to the threat Nxf7:} 22. Nxf7 Rxh4 23. Rxh4 Ng6 {[%csl Gf7,
Gh4]}) ({The previously played} 14. Ng5 $5 {did not cross my mind either:} Nxf4
(14... Be7 $2 15. Nxe6 $1 Qxe6 16. f5 Nf4 17. Qf3 $1 Qxf5 18. Nxd5 $16) 15. Qf3
Ng6 16. Rhf1 Nd8 17. Bg3 h4 18. Bh2 c6 {White has serious pressure, but in the
absence of pawn breaks it is not obvious how he can make further progress. In
