1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 b6 5. a3 Bf8 6. Nf3 {This is the most
consistent move, continuing development without making any important
commitment.} Ne7 {The same comment applies to this move, and now White is at a
crossroads. In this section we will investigate some minor lines.} 7. b4 {
This is based on a small trick not available after 6.b4 examined earlier, but
is not dangerous either.} (7. Ne2 Ba6 (7... c5 8. c3 Ba6 {is also possible.})
8. Nf4 Bxf1 9. Kxf1 h5 (9... g6 10. g4 c5 11. c3 Nbc6 12. Kg2 c4 13. Ne2 h6 14.
Bf4 Qd7 15. Bg3 Bg7 16. h3 O-O-O 17. Nd2 f6 $132 18. exf6 $6 Bxf6 19. f4 g5 20.
Nf3 Ng6 {with black initiative, Dolmatov,S (2545)-Gulko,B (2590) Frunze 
(Kirgiziya) 1981 (1/2-1/2, 34).}) 10. Qd3 Nbc6 ({Black could also start
playing in the centre with} 10... c5 {, since he has enough resources after}
11. c4 Nbc6 12. cxd5 Nxd5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. Qe4 Rb8 $11) 11. Bd2 Qd7 12. g3 Nf5
13. h3 Be7 14. Kg2 O-O-O 15. g4 (15. h4 Kb7 16. a4 {is more consistent,
leading to a position with mutual chances.}) 15... hxg4 16. hxg4 Nh6 17. Kg3 g5
18. Nh5 f5 19. exf6 e5 $17 {Fedorowicz,J (2520)-Gulko,B (2565) Estes Park 1987
(1/2-1/2, 38)}) (7. Bg5 h6 8. Bxe7 Bxe7 {is an obvious concession.} 9. Bd3 c5
10. O-O Nc6 11. Re1 c4 12. Bf1 a6 13. Ne2 b5 $11 14. g4 $6 h5 15. h3 hxg4 16.
hxg4 Bd7 17. Ng3 Qc7 18. Kg2 f6 19. Qd2 fxe5 20. dxe5 O-O-O 21. b3 Rdf8 22. Qe3
Rxf3 23. Qxf3 Bc5 24. b4 Nxe5 25. Qf4 Bd6 26. Qg5 Rh2+ $1 {0-1 Fluvia Poyatos,
J (2491)-Prasca Sosa,R (2415) Badalona 2012}) (7. Bf4 {is mainly intended to
meet ...c7-c5 with Nb5, but Black can deal with that.} Bd7 $5 $146 {A
prophylactic move, ensuring that the knight will be under attack a few moves
later.} (7... c5 8. Nb5 Nf5 9. c3 a6 10. g4 axb5 11. gxf5 $14) 8. Bd3 (8. h4 c5
9. Nb5 Nf5 10. c3 c4 $11) 8... c5 9. Nb5 (9. b3 Nbc6 10. Nb5 Ng6 11. Bg3 a6
$132) 9... Nf5 10. c3 a6 11. Bxf5 Bxb5 12. a4 Bd7 13. Bd3 c4 14. Bc2 Nc6 15.
O-O h6 $11 {, followed by ...b5.}) 7... c5 8. Bg5 {This is the point. White
threatens Nb5.} a6 $1 {Solving all of the problems.} 9. Ne2 (9. bxc5 bxc5 10.
dxc5 h6 11. Bd2 Nd7 12. Bd3 Nc6 13. Qe2 Nxc5 $15 {Tal,M (2620)-Dizdar,G (2455)
Jurmala (Latvia) 1983 (1/2-1/2, 28)}) 9... cxd4 $1 $146 {It is better to
exchange in the centre with the bishop still on g5.} (9... h6 10. Bd2 {Klovans,
J-Dizdar,G (2455) Jurmala (Latvia) 1983 (1-0, 36)} cxd4 $5 11. Nfxd4 Nbc6 12.
f4 $11) 10. Nexd4 ({The difference is that} 10. Nfxd4 Qc7 11. f4 {runs into}
Ng6 {followed by ...h6.}) 10... h6 {Now is a good moment to drive away the
bishop.} 11. Be3 Nd7 12. Bd3 g5 13. h3 Bg7 14. O-O Qc7 $11 {with mutual
chances.} *

