10... Qb8 (10... h6 $2 11. Nb5 $1 $18) 11. Nb5 Ng6 12. c4 {Again, the only way
to maintain the rhythm.} a6 13. cxd5 axb5 14. dxc6 Bxc6 {An interesting
position in which White has to play with energy and inspiration.} 15. d5 $5 (
15. Qc2 Qb7 16. d5 Bxd5 17. Bxb5+ Bc6 18. Qe4 Rc8 19. Rfd1 Be7 20. Bxe7 Nxe7
21. Rd6 h6 22. Rad1 O-O $11) 15... exd5 16. h4 (16. Qc2 Qc7 17. e6 Bd6 18.
exf7+ Kxf7 19. h4 Kg8 20. Rae1 Ne5 21. Nxe5 Bxe5 22. f4 Bd4+ 23. Kh1 Re8 $13 {
White's compensation for the pawn is real but not that threatening.}) 16... Be7
17. h5 Bxg5 18. Nxg5 Nf4 {Aiming for a blockade on e6.} (18... Nxe5 19. f4 Nxd3
20. Qxd3 $16 {offers White too much initiative.}) 19. Bxh7 Kf8 20. Re1 Ne6 21.
Nxe6+ fxe6 22. Bg6 Be8 $11 *

