g6 16. g4 Ng7 {[%cal Gc5c4,Ge8d7,Gd7c7,Gb6b5,Gb5b4] Black has stopped White's
pawn attack and can think of his own already. He may block the queenside with .
..c5-c4 followed by the king's transfer to c7 and ...b5-b4.}) 11... Nfxd4 12.
Nxd4 Nxd4 13. Bxd4 cxd4 14. Bb5+ (14. Ne2 O-O 15. g3 (15. Nxd4 Bh4+ 16. Kd1 f6
$17) 15... d3 16. Qxd3 b5 $5 17. Nd4 (17. Qxb5 Bd7 18. Qd3 f6 $17) 17... Qb6)
14... Bd7 15. Bxd7+ Qxd7 16. Ne2 Rc8 17. O-O-O Rc4 18. Nxd4 Bc5 {With strong
counterplay.} *

