{[#]White has decided to annihilate Black's achievements in the centre with 14.
c4. Is there any way for Black to retain the initiative?} 14... dxc4 $1 {
The strongest move, aiming at keeping the pawn on c4.} (14... Bxc4 15. Bxc4
dxc4 16. Qc2 {is safe enough for White.}) 15. Be4 Nc6 16. Qa4 Nb4 $1 {The clue
to Black's previous play. By sacrificing an exchange Black obtains a clear
domination... and two pawns!.} (16... Bb7 17. Qxc4 {is once again acceptable
for White.}) 17. Qxd7+ Kxd7 18. Bxa8 Nd3+ 19. Kd2 Rxa8 20. Ke3 Nxb2 $17 {
The bishops' pair, two pawns, the outpost on d3 are much more valuable than
the exchange, Van der Wiel,J (2540)-Portisch,L (2630) Tilburg 1988 (0-1, 43)} *

